    "title": "Java springdoc-openapi show LocalDateTime field with additional date/time fields in Swagger UI Example Value",
    "body": "<p>spring-boot 2.6.2<br />\nspringdoc-openapi 1.6.2</p>\n<p><strong>Single</strong> field <code>LocalDateTime dateTime</code> in body represent in Swagger UI Example Value as</p>\n<pre><code>{\n  &quot;dateTime&quot;: &quot;2022-01-21T10:02:46.481Z&quot;,\n  &quot;time&quot;: {\n    &quot;hour&quot;: 0,\n    &quot;minute&quot;: 0,\n    &quot;second&quot;: 0,\n    &quot;nano&quot;: 0\n  },\n  &quot;date&quot;: &quot;2022-01-21&quot;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Date format can be fixed (<a href=\"https://ru.stackoverflow.com/a/1276885/209226\">https://ru.stackoverflow.com/a/1276885/209226</a>) by</p>\n<pre><code>    static {\n        var schema = new Schema&lt;LocalTime&gt;();\n        schema.example(LocalTime.now().format(DateTimeFormatter.ISO_TIME));\n        SpringDocUtils.getConfig().replaceWithSchema(LocalTime.class, schema);\n    }\n</code></pre>\n<p>But it is still remained 3 fields iso one <code>dateTime</code>:</p>\n<pre><code>{\n  &quot;dateTime&quot;: &quot;2022-01-21T10:05:52.945Z&quot;,\n  &quot;time&quot;: &quot;13:05:14.746&quot;,\n  &quot;date&quot;: &quot;2022-01-21&quot;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>How can it be fixed?</p>\n"
  },
  "answers": [
    {
      "owner": {
        "account_id": 13990306,
        "reputation": 80,
        "user_id": 10104424,
        "user_type": "registered",
        "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c1f221ac3c537f034a1c560d42cc1d31?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
        "display_name": "Zack789",
        "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10104424/zack789"
      },
      "is_accepted": false,
      "score": 1,
      "last_activity_date": 1660905873,
      "creation_date": 1660905873,
      "answer_id": 73415552,
      "question_id": 70799677,
      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>For Kotlin Developer:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-kotlin prettyprint-override\"><code>@Configuration\nopen class SwaggerConfig{\n    init {\n        val schema: Schema&lt;LocalDateTime&gt; = Schema&lt;LocalDateTime&gt;()\n        schema.example(LocalDateTime.now().format(DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(&quot;yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss&quot;)))\n        SpringDocUtils.getConfig().replaceWithSchema(LocalDateTime::class.java, schema)\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
    },
    {
      "owner": {
        "account_id": 15460945,
        "reputation": 41,
        "user_id": 11153658,
        "user_type": "registered",
        "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Cw6g66EFX04/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABc/z0j6c3c95Qg/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
        "display_name": "Yacine Sghairi",
        "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11153658/yacine-sghairi"
      },
      "is_accepted": false,
      "score": 4,
      "last_activity_date": 1660223653,
      "creation_date": 1660223653,
      "answer_id": 73321304,
      "question_id": 70799677,
      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>if you want a better representation you need to add a type, in my case string.\nSee Docs (<a href=\"https://swagger.io/specification/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://swagger.io/specification/</a>)</p>\n<pre><code>static {\n            var schema = new Schema&lt;LocalTime&gt;();\n            schema.example(LocalTime.now().format(DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(&quot;HH:mm:ss&quot;))).type(&quot;string&quot;);\n            SpringDocUtils.getConfig().replaceWithSchema(LocalTime.class, schema);\n        }\n</code></pre>\n"
    }
